n circles show categorical oscillatory distribution. Both curves follow $$n(\omega ) \propto [\exp (\hbar \omega /k_B T) - 1]^{-1}$$ for low frequencies ($$\omega < 10^{13}$$ rad/s), exhibiting high occupation ($$n \sim 10^4$$). At high frequencies ($$\omega > 10^{14}$$ rad/s), occupation drops precipitously ($$n < 10^{-6}$$), demonstrating quantum cutoff. Categorical distribution reproduces Bose-Einstein statistics exactly, confirming thermodynamic consistency}{figure.18}{}}
